      <Value><![CDATA[<div class="page">
<div class="layoutArea">
<div class="column">
<p><span class="lead"><strong>Slide Titles</strong></span></p>
<p>Ensure each slide has a unique title. People who have a visual impairment or a reading disability rely on slide titles to navigate. For example, by skimming or using a screen reader, they can quickly scan through a list of slide titles and go right to the slide they want.</p>
<p>Help: <a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/office/make-your-powerpoint-presentations-accessible-to-people-with-disabilities-6f7772b2-2f33-4bd2-8ca7-dae3b2b3ef25?ocmsassetid=ha102013555&amp;correlationid=a49fc64e-4629-495e-9116-a6024833e469&amp;ui=en-us&amp;rs=en-us&amp;ad=us" title="Using the unique slide titles" data-anchor="?ocmsassetid=ha102013555&amp;correlationid=a49fc64e-4629-495e-9116-a6024833e469&amp;ui=en-us&amp;rs=en-us&amp;ad=us">Using unique slide titles</a></p>
<p><span class="lead"><strong>Fonts </strong></span></p>
<div class="page">
<div class="layoutArea">
<div class="column">
<p>Ensure that font size is sufficiently large—generally a minimum of 18 points. Use Sans Serif fonts such as Arial or Verdana.</p>
<p>Help: <a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/office/make-your-powerpoint-presentations-accessible-to-people-with-disabilities-6f7772b2-2f33-4bd2-8ca7-dae3b2b3ef25?ocmsassetid=ha102013555&amp;correlationid=a49fc64e-4629-495e-9116-a6024833e469&amp;ui=en-us&amp;rs=en-us&amp;ad=us" title="Formatting Text for accessibility" data-anchor="?ocmsassetid=ha102013555&amp;correlationid=a49fc64e-4629-495e-9116-a6024833e469&amp;ui=en-us&amp;rs=en-us&amp;ad=us">Formatting text for accessibility </a></p>
<div class="page">
<div class="layoutArea">
<div class="column">
<p><span class="lead"><strong>Contrast and Colour</strong></span></p>
<p>Ensure there is good contrast between elements on the page, e.g. text and background colours. Use a simple background.<br />Do not use colour as the only way to convey information on a slide.</p>
<p>Help: <a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/office/make-your-powerpoint-presentations-accessible-to-people-with-disabilities-6f7772b2-2f33-4bd2-8ca7-dae3b2b3ef25?ocmsassetid=ha102013555&amp;correlationid=a49fc64e-4629-495e-9116-a6024833e469&amp;ui=en-us&amp;rs=en-us&amp;ad=us" title="accessibility text colours" data-anchor="?ocmsassetid=ha102013555&amp;correlationid=a49fc64e-4629-495e-9116-a6024833e469&amp;ui=en-us&amp;rs=en-us&amp;ad=us"> accessibility text color </a></p>
<div class="page">
<div class="layoutArea">
<div class="column">
<div class="page">
<div class="layoutArea">
<div class="column">
<p><span class="lead"><strong>General Content</strong></span></p>
<p>Limit the amount of information on slides and avoid long sentences.</p>
<p>Unless important for the slide, avoid animations and automatic slide transitions as they can be distracting or work incorrectly with Screen Readers.</p>
<div class="page">
<div class="layoutArea">
<div class="column">
<p><span class="lead"><strong>Links</strong></span></p>
<p>Use descriptive link text for links, when linking to web pages within your documents. Avoid text such as ‘Read More’ or ‘Click Here’. Links should convey clear and accurate information about the destination.</p>
<p>Help: <a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/office/make-your-powerpoint-presentations-accessible-to-people-with-disabilities-6f7772b2-2f33-4bd2-8ca7-dae3b2b3ef25?ocmsassetid=ha102013555&amp;correlationid=a49fc64e-4629-495e-9116-a6024833e469&amp;ui=en-us&amp;rs=en-us&amp;ad=us" title="Adding hyperlinks text and screen tips" data-anchor="?ocmsassetid=ha102013555&amp;correlationid=a49fc64e-4629-495e-9116-a6024833e469&amp;ui=en-us&amp;rs=en-us&amp;ad=us"> Adding hyperlinks text and screen tips </a></p>
<div class="page">
<div class="layoutArea">
<div class="column">
<p><span class="lead"><strong>Tables</strong></span></p>
<p>Use a simple table structure, and specify column header information.</p>
<p>Ensure that tables do not contain split cells, merged cells, nested tables, or completely blank rows or columns.</p>
<p>Do not use tables to format layout, only for presenting data. Use alternative text descriptions for tables.</p>
<p>Help: <a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/office/make-your-powerpoint-presentations-accessible-to-people-with-disabilities-6f7772b2-2f33-4bd2-8ca7-dae3b2b3ef25?ocmsassetid=ha102013555&amp;correlationid=a49fc64e-4629-495e-9116-a6024833e469&amp;ui=en-us&amp;rs=en-us&amp;ad=us" title="Adding hyperlinks text and screen tips" data-anchor="?ocmsassetid=ha102013555&amp;correlationid=a49fc64e-4629-495e-9116-a6024833e469&amp;ui=en-us&amp;rs=en-us&amp;ad=us"> How to use table headers </a></p>
<p>Help: <a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/office/make-your-powerpoint-presentations-accessible-to-people-with-disabilities-6f7772b2-2f33-4bd2-8ca7-dae3b2b3ef25?ocmsassetid=ha102013555&amp;correlationid=a49fc64e-4629-495e-9116-a6024833e469&amp;ui=en-us&amp;rs=en-us&amp;ad=us" title="Adding hyperlinks text and screen tips" data-anchor="?ocmsassetid=ha102013555&amp;correlationid=a49fc64e-4629-495e-9116-a6024833e469&amp;ui=en-us&amp;rs=en-us&amp;ad=us"> Adding alt text to tables </a></p>
<div class="page">
<div class="layoutArea">
<div class="column">
<p><span class="lead"><strong>Images</strong></span></p>
<p>Provide alternative labels for all images. To do this, right-click on the image, then select Format Picture and then select ‘Alt Text’.</p>
<p>Alternative text (Alt Text) describes an object so that a user’s assistive technology may convey the information being shown. The text should communicate the purpose of the image or other object accurately and succinctly.</p>
<p>Help: <a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/office/make-your-powerpoint-presentations-accessible-to-people-with-disabilities-6f7772b2-2f33-4bd2-8ca7-dae3b2b3ef25?ocmsassetid=ha102013555&amp;correlationid=a49fc64e-4629-495e-9116-a6024833e469&amp;ui=en-us&amp;rs=en-us&amp;ad=us" title="Adding hyperlinks text and screen tips" data-anchor="?ocmsassetid=ha102013555&amp;correlationid=a49fc64e-4629-495e-9116-a6024833e469&amp;ui=en-us&amp;rs=en-us&amp;ad=us"> How to add alt text to images </a></p>
<p>Help: <a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/office/make-your-powerpoint-presentations-accessible-to-people-with-disabilities-6f7772b2-2f33-4bd2-8ca7-dae3b2b3ef25?ocmsassetid=ha102013555&amp;correlationid=a49fc64e-4629-495e-9116-a6024833e469&amp;ui=en-us&amp;rs=en-us&amp;ad=us" title="Adding hyperlinks text and screen tips" data-anchor="?ocmsassetid=ha102013555&amp;correlationid=a49fc64e-4629-495e-9116-a6024833e469&amp;ui=en-us&amp;rs=en-us&amp;ad=us"> improving images accessibility in PowerPoint </a></p>
<div class="page">
<div class="layoutArea">
<div class="column">
<div class="page">
<div class="layoutArea">
<div class="column">
<p><span class="lead"><strong>Embedded Video and Audio</strong></span></p>
<p>If you have embedded video, ensure the video is captioned and the player controls are accessible.</p>
<p>For an audio only file, a transcription should be included.</p>
<p>Help: <a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/office/make-your-powerpoint-presentations-accessible-to-people-with-disabilities-6f7772b2-2f33-4bd2-8ca7-dae3b2b3ef25?ocmsassetid=ha102013555&amp;correlationid=a49fc64e-4629-495e-9116-a6024833e469&amp;ui=en-us&amp;rs=en-us&amp;ad=us" title="Using captions, subtitles and alternative audio tracks in videos" data-anchor="?ocmsassetid=ha102013555&amp;correlationid=a49fc64e-4629-495e-9116-a6024833e469&amp;ui=en-us&amp;rs=en-us&amp;ad=us"> Using captions, subtitles and alternative audio tracks in videos </a></p>
<p>Help: <a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/office/make-your-powerpoint-presentations-accessible-to-people-with-disabilities-6f7772b2-2f33-4bd2-8ca7-dae3b2b3ef25?ocmsassetid=ha102013555&amp;correlationid=a49fc64e-4629-495e-9116-a6024833e469&amp;ui=en-us&amp;rs=en-us&amp;ad=us" title="How to Quickly Record Narration in PowerPoint" data-anchor="?ocmsassetid=ha102013555&amp;correlationid=a49fc64e-4629-495e-9116-a6024833e469&amp;ui=en-us&amp;rs=en-us&amp;ad=us"> How to Quickly Record Narration in PowerPoint </a></p>
<div class="page">
<div class="layoutArea">
<div class="column">
<p><span class="lead"><strong>Converting a PowerPoint to PDF format</strong></span></p>
<p>Whilst PowerPoint is great for presentations, it is not usually the best format for content on the web. Converting the PowerPoint to a PDF is often a better way to distribute the presentation electronically. Assuming the original PowerPoint has been created following these guidelines, most accessibility features will be retained in the PDF file.</p>
<p>Help: <a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/office/make-your-powerpoint-presentations-accessible-to-people-with-disabilities-6f7772b2-2f33-4bd2-8ca7-dae3b2b3ef25?ocmsassetid=ha102013555&amp;correlationid=a49fc64e-4629-495e-9116-a6024833e469&amp;ui=en-us&amp;rs=en-us&amp;ad=us" title="How to Quickly Record Narration in PowerPoint" data-anchor="?ocmsassetid=ha102013555&amp;correlationid=a49fc64e-4629-495e-9116-a6024833e469&amp;ui=en-us&amp;rs=en-us&amp;ad=us"> How to save a PowerPoint presentation as a PDF </a></p>
<div class="page">
<div class="layoutArea">
<div class="column">
<div class="page">
<div class="layoutArea">
<div class="column">
<p><span class="lead"><strong>Accessibility Checker</strong></span></p>
<p>Use Microsoft PowerPoint’s built in Accessibility Checker function. It inspects your file and alerts you to issues that could make it difficult for a user with a disability to access.</p>
<p>It can be found under File / Info / Check for Issues / Check Accessibility.</p>
<p>Help: <a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/office/make-your-powerpoint-presentations-accessible-to-people-with-disabilities-6f7772b2-2f33-4bd2-8ca7-dae3b2b3ef25?ocmsassetid=ha102013555&amp;correlationid=a49fc64e-4629-495e-9116-a6024833e469&amp;ui=en-us&amp;rs=en-us&amp;ad=us" title="Using the built in Accessibility checker" data-anchor="?ocmsassetid=ha102013555&amp;correlationid=a49fc64e-4629-495e-9116-a6024833e469&amp;ui=en-us&amp;rs=en-us&amp;ad=us"> Using the built in Accessibility checker </a></p>
<div class="page">
<div class="layoutArea">
<div class="column">
<p><span class="lead"><strong>Other Useful Resources</strong></span></p>
<div class="page">
<div class="layoutArea">
<div class="column">
<p><a href="https://webaim.org/techniques/powerpoint/" title="PowerPoint Accessibility">WebAIM PowerPoint Accessibility Article</a></p>
