    <introduction>
      <Value><![CDATA[<div class="page">
<div class="layoutArea">
<div class="column">
<p><span class="lead">Top Tips for Producing Accessible PowerPoint Presentations</span></p>
<div class="page">
<div class="layoutArea">
<div class="column">
<p><span class="lead"><strong>Slide Layout</strong></span></p>
<p>Make sure slide contents can be read in the order that you intend. Screen readers may sometimes read the elements of a slide in a different order from the way things appear on the screen.</p>
<div class="page">
<div class="layoutArea">
<div class="column">
<p>Use one of PowerPoint’s pre-set accessible layouts from the Home/New Slide option.</p>
<p>Help: <a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/office/make-your-powerpoint-presentations-accessible-to-people-with-disabilities-6f7772b2-2f33-4bd2-8ca7-dae3b2b3ef25?ocmsassetid=ha102013555&amp;correlationid=a49fc64e-4629-495e-9116-a6024833e469&amp;ui=en-us&amp;rs=en-us&amp;ad=us" title="Setting the reading order of slide contents" data-anchor="?ocmsassetid=ha102013555&amp;correlationid=a49fc64e-4629-495e-9116-a6024833e469&amp;ui=en-us&amp;rs=en-us&amp;ad=us">Setting the reading order of slide contents</a></p>
<p>Help: <a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/office/make-your-powerpoint-presentations-accessible-to-people-with-disabilities-6f7772b2-2f33-4bd2-8ca7-dae3b2b3ef25?ocmsassetid=ha102013555&amp;correlationid=a49fc64e-4629-495e-9116-a6024833e469&amp;ui=en-us&amp;rs=en-us&amp;ad=us" title="Make your PowerPoint presentations accessible to people with disabilities" data-anchor="?ocmsassetid=ha102013555&amp;correlationid=a49fc64e-4629-495e-9116-a6024833e469&amp;ui=en-us&amp;rs=en-us&amp;ad=us">Using built-in slide designs for inclusive reading order</a></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>]]></Value>
